# [\#14156 PR](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/pull/14156) `merged`: Fix Remix links by adding `#` before URL params
**Labels**: `documentation :book:`, `external contribution :star:`


#### <img src="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/13069972?u=026ff4eade3b02c5d4810551aa390b58d439ec46&v=4" width="50">[kuzdogan](https://github.com/kuzdogan) opened issue at [2023-04-26 08:44](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/pull/14156):

Looks like Remix actually uses a `#` before the query params, as laid out in docs: https://remix-ide.readthedocs.io/en/latest/locations.html#load-an-encoded-base64-string-into-a-sol-file-in-the-editor

For most of the links this works fine without `#` but I noticed this when I got a `413` from the following ERC20 example on the [Yul page](https://docs.soliditylang.org/en/latest/yul.html#complete-erc20-example): 

[LINK](https://remix.ethereum.org/?language=yul&version=0.8.20&
)
```
https://remix.ethereum.org/?language=yul&version=0.8.20&
```

By adding a `#` the link starts working
[Working Link](https://remix.ethereum.org/?#language=yul&version=0.8.20&)
```
https://remix.ethereum.org/?#language=yul&version=0.8.20&
```

Just note that the "Working link" redirects to the following link. 
```
https://remix.ethereum.org/?#language=yul&version=soljson-v0.8.18+commit.87f61d96.js&&lang=en&optimize=false&runs=200&evmVersion=null
```

The "version" parameter is changed to `soljson-v0.8.18+commit.87f61d96.js` and Remix appends `&lang=en&optimize=false&runs=200&evmVersion=null`. 

I don't think this needs any changes as it works but the version provided by the link in the Solidity docs is not in correct form.

#### <img src="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/137030?v=4" width="50">[cameel](https://github.com/cameel) commented at [2023-05-01 18:25](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/pull/14156#issuecomment-1530045874):

This new URL format must be a recent addition. Back when we added Remix links, the docs were showing the one that we use.

And HTTP 413 is just a consequence of some of our code snippets URL being too long for some browsers or proxies when base-64 encoded. In this case it's a CloudFlare limit. There's not much we can do about that limit on our side other than maybe not create links for these snippets (see #13302). In this new URL format the code is processed client-side so I guess this could be workaround they came up with to fix this. If that's the case then nice.

> The "version" parameter is changed to `soljson-v0.8.18+commit.87f61d96.js` and Remix appends `&lang=en&optimize=false&runs=200&evmVersion=null`.

This looks like a bug in Remix side. It definitely should be fixed. Our docs intentionally use versions for these snippets so that when you look at a snippet in older docs and follow the link, you get a compiler that can actually compile it. Now that this PR is merged, this is broken. I think it would have been better to hold off with this change until this works properly in Remix.

Pinging @Aniket-Engg.

> version provided by the link in the Solidity docs is not in correct form.

It's correct. It intentionally has no hash, because getting that when building docs on RTD is problematic. Remix already has a compiler list so it's much easier to resolve there. I specifically asked for that feature and they implemented it for us: https://github.com/ethereum/remix-project/issues/1490
